Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the secrecy capacity and outage performance of wireless communication systems, which are key topics in information theory.
2. cs.GT (Game Theory) - The concept of secrecy in communication systems involves game-theoretic considerations between the legitimate transmitter and the eavesdropper, making this sub-category a possibility.
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with wireless communication systems, which are a part of networking and internet architecture.
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper deals with the security aspect of wireless communication systems, making this sub-category a possibility.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - Although less likely, the paper deals with the performance of wireless communication systems, which can be considered a part of multimedia systems.
